'''Wikispaces''' is a [[Free web hosting service|hosting service]] (sometimes called a [[wiki farm]]) based in [[San Francisco, California]]. Launched in March 2005, Wikispaces is owned by Tangient [[Limited liability company|LLC]] and is among the largest wiki hosts, competing with [[PBworks]], [[Wetpaint]], [[Wikia]], and [[Google Sites]] (formerly JotSpot).<ref>''Veni, Vidi, Wiki" ''Wired'' (2006)</ref>
Private wikis with advanced features for businesses, non-profits and educators are available for an annual fee. As of March 2008, they had more than 920,000 registered members and hosted more than 390,000 wikis.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.wikispaces.com/2008/03/wikispaces-turns-three.html |title=Wikispaces Turns Three |date=March 1, 2008 |work=blog.wikispaces.com }}</ref> By March 2009, that number had increased to over 2.2 million registered members and more than 900,000 wikis.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.wikispaces.com/2009/03/wikispaces-birthday-site-statistics.html |title=Wikispaces Birthday Week: Site Statistics |date=March 18, 2009 |work=blog.wikispaces.com }}</ref> Wikispaces has also given away more than 100,000 premium wikis to [[K-12]] educators.<ref>"A quarter million teachers to get free wikis" CNET (2008)</ref>
Since 2010 Wikispaces have cooperated with web 2.0 education platform [[Glogster EDU]]. Glogster EDU embeds Glogs into Wikispaces services.
